title: JetBlue baggage fee leaves Southwest as last holdout
text:
JetBlue baggage fee leaves Southwest as last holdout Related Items Enlarge Image Request to buy this photo Eamon Queeney | Dispatch Todd Hassinger, left, and Howard Jefferson, center, unload baggage from a Southwest Airlines flight at Port Columbus International Airport. Southwest is the only major airline that does not charge a fee for a passenger’s first two checked bags. From wire reports • Wednesday July 1, 2015 12:25 AM 
LONG ISLAND CITY, N.Y. — The era of free checked suitcases on JetBlue has come to an end. 
The airline proudly proclaimed itself a holdout on fees for years, allowing passengers to check one bag free. 
Now, JetBlue will charge up to $25 for checked luggage. 
The fee only applies to new bookings; existing reservations still get one free bag. 
The move leaves Southwest Airlines as the only major U.S. carrier not to charge a bag fee.
